CELL SUSPENSION ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
CELL SUSPENSION NAME: A short, descriptive name for the biomaterial that need not be unique.
CELL SUSPENSION DESCRIPTION: A general description of the biomaterial.
GENUS SPECIES (Required): The scientific binomial name for the species of the suspension.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
SELECTED CELL TYPE(S): The cell type(s) selected to be present in the suspension.
SELECTED CELL TYPE(S) ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
SELECTED CELL TYPE(S) ONTOLOGY LABEL ONT: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
ESTIMATED CELL COUNT: Estimated number of cells in the suspension.
